
---


@startuml

' Define classes
class Cinema {
  +id: int
  +name: string
  +theatres: List<Theatre>
}

class Theatre {
  +id: int
  +name: string
  +seats: int
  +copies: List<MovieCopy>
}

class MovieCopy {
  +id: int
  +movie: Movie
  +cinema: Cinema
  +location: Cinema
}

class Movie {
  +id: int
  +title: string
  +duration: int
}

class Show {
  +id: int
  +movie: Movie
  +theatre: Theatre
  +startTime: DateTime
  +endTime: DateTime
  +published: boolean
}

class ShowProgram {
  +id: int
  +shows: List<Show>
  +weekStart: DateTime
}

class Customer {
  +id: int
  +name: string
  +email: string
}

class Reservation {
  +id: int
  +customer: Customer
  +show: Show
  +seatNumber: int
  +status: Status
}

enum Status {
  PENDING, CONFIRMED, CANCELLED, EXPIRED
}

class Offer {
  +id: int
  +reservation: Reservation
  +newShow: Show
  +newSeatNumber: int
  +expirationTime: DateTime
}

class Ticket {
  +id: int
  +show: Show
  +seatNumber: int
  +customer: Customer
  +isReserved: boolean
}

' Relationships
Cinema "1" -- "0..*" Theatre : has
Theatre "1" -- "1" MovieCopy : contains
MovieCopy "1" -- "1" Movie : copies
Movie "1" -- "0..*" Show : used in
Show "1" -- "1" Theatre : occurs in
Show "1" -- "1" ShowProgram : part of
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Reservation : made by
Reservation "1" -- "1" Show : for
Reservation "1" -- "0..1" Offer : associated with
Offer "1" -- "1" Show : offers seat in
Offer "1" -- "1" Reservation : related to
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Ticket : purchased by
Ticket "1" -- "1" Show : for
Ticket "1" -- "1" Seat : assigned to

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:

- **Cinema** owns several **Theatres**, which contain **MovieCopies**.
- Each **MovieCopy** belongs to a specific **Cinema** and can be moved between Cinemas.
- A **Show** is scheduled in a specific **Theatre** and uses a **Movie**.
- A **ShowProgram** represents a weekly schedule (from Wednesday to Tuesday).
- **Reservations** are made by **Customers** for **Shows**.
- **Offers** are created when a reservation is cancelled or if a show is removed.
- **Tickets** are issued at the entrance for shows without reservations.
- The **Status** enum tracks the state of a reservation (e.g., pending, confirmed, etc.).

